&lt;p&gt;The Estates and Facilities Department covers a very large and diverse range of duties, which means that you would interact closely with many stakeholder groups on a wide range of matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work Monday to Friday, as part of a small proactive team of NHSBT staff and contractors who are customer focussed and have a can-do attitude, enabling colleagues across the organisation to carry out their duties efficiently and effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Estates &amp; Facilities team makes a real contribution to saving and improving lives and have a major impact on the Donor Experience what could be better than that?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will undertake an extensive induction and training programme and receive ongoing development to support you in your role and achieving your career ambitions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information contact Stephen Ojo – &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;stephen.ojo@nhsbt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
